{"type":"system","subtype":"task_started","task_id":"a18efa91bde57eaad","tool_use_id":"toolu_016vMXm965JDYqz841kU7bii","description":"Review implementation completeness","task_type":"local_agent","prompt":"Review the uncommitted changes in lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts and the new file lib/text-classifier/food-dictionary.ts for implementation completeness.\n\nContext: These changes implement dictionary-guided OCR repair for a recipe title extractor. The improvement plan is at tools/title-loop/docs/24-b15aa30/improvement-plan.md.\n\nSpecifically check:\n1. Is `repairOcrText` actually called in all the right places in `buildCandidates`? Does it cover single-line, 2-line join, and 3-line join candidates?\n2. Is the `isTitleAbsentPage` guard actually filtering candidates effectively? Check the logic flow — does `titleAbsent` flag actually prevent bad selections?\n3. Does the bilingual layout boost at ~line 1050 actually fire when expected? Check the conditions carefully.\n4. Does the compound title dedup protection at ~line 1238 actually prevent the removal described in the plan?\n5. Is the `OCR_SUBSTITUTIONS` map complete for the cases mentioned in the plan? The plan mentions `1→i`, `1→l`, `0→o`, `4→a`, `5→s`, `¡→i`, `Í→i`.\n\nRun: git diff HEAD lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts\nAnd read both files. Do NOT suggest modifications — just report findings.","uuid":"28347091-2dcb-47f9-ab2f-d11bb016110d","session_id":"ec54b805-2592-4abe-8e4f-4011b51bb626"}
